  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cf79f57f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Prophet Model for Daily Rat Sightings in New York City"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7adc7aaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For ease, we reimport the data. This way, we can run only the code in this section as opposed to having to run the code blocks above."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 130,
   "id": "8d48638c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from prophet.plot import plot_plotly, plot_components_plotly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b65db25a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Tuning Hyperparameters for Prophet"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f71b08d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We make a copy of rs and set df as a copy of rs. This is so we don't mix up our variables. We will tune hyperparameters using df in the code below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 131,
   "id": "d85b9fae",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rs_saved = rs.copy()\n",
    "df = rs.copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 132,
   "id": "17c7f466",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Adding in holidays\n",
    "\n",
    "date_range = pd.date_range(start=\"2020-01-01\", end=\"2026-02-28\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate US federal holidays\n",
    "calendar = USFederalHolidayCalendar()\n",
    "holidays = calendar.holidays(start=date_range.min(), end=date_range.max())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build the DataFrame in the same structure as your original\n",
    "federal_holidays = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'holiday': 'federal_us',\n",
    "    'ds': pd.to_datetime(holidays),\n",
    "    'lower_window': 0,\n",
    "    'upper_window': 1,\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "holidays = federal_holidays"
   ]
  },
